PCA was performed to summarise the data with a multivariate approach and to provide a visual representation of the reciprocal phenotypic distance. The first three components, explaining 74.22% of the total variance, were selected for data interpretation. Characterisation of Principal Components (PCs) was performed by calculating the correlation coefficients with the original traits and the associated significance level (Table 3). Moreover, one-way ANOVA models were constructed including the Principal Components as response variables and grain shape, time of release, phylogenetic group, and flag leaf attitude as explanatory variables (see Methods section); coefficients of determination (R2) and related p-values were reported in Supplementary Table S1; the categories coefficient estimates, tested for significant differences from zero (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
