				\begin{document}$$(95 \% C{I}_{median}=Median\pm 1.57\cdot \frac{IQR}{\sqrt{n}}),$$\end{document}(95%CImedian=Median±1.57⋅IQRn),where IQR is the interquartile range and n the sampling number. The medians of two groups are (roughly) significantly different at a 95% confidence level when their notches do not overlap. Boxplot figures were created using ggplot2 R Package48.

